JQuery supplies some of the features supplied by the jQuery
language. It supplies an easy interface for Ajax, and some widgets.

Examples and documentation is included.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install

To run the tests, you will need to point your web server to the
correct directories.

An example:

    The JQuery files on my system were installed in 
     /usr/lib/perl5/site_perl/5.8.8/JQuery

    So I added the following two line to the apache configuration
    file:

    DocumentRoot  /usr/lib/perl5/site_perl/5.8.8/JQuery
    ScriptAlias /cgi-bin/  /usr/lib/perl5/site_perl/5.8.8/JQuery/cgi-bin/



SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc JQuery

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/JQuery

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=JQuery

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/JQuery

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/JQuery

